      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Judge Julius Mack, whose recent\ndecision at Chicago, holding that a\nsympathetic strike is boycott and,\ntherefore, Illegal, has always been\nconsidered fair to organized labor,\nand while there are many who will\nquestion the wisdom and constitu-\ntionality of the decision, there will\nbe few, who know the Judge, who\nwill dobt his honesty o. integrity.\nMembers of unions in this city\nwhen their attention was called to\nthe decision said they could not see\nhow the courts could compel man\nto work if he did not feel like do\ning so."
    }
